* Dinobot stalked low between the ancient trees, the mist had thickened 
again and he had to rely on his hearing and smell in order to track.         
                                                   He crept quietly and kept 
in mind to keep low, you never could tell when a Predacon might jump out 
from behind a tree and open fire!
Dinobot smiled mentally to himself, once he was fully healed he wouldn't 
care if an entire Predacon fleet jumped out at him.
He was surprised at how quickly the urge to fight came again when he had 
just finished one a mega-cycle and a half ago, he snarled.
Dinobot had left it up to his Beast Mode to repair him, there was no point 
in wasting spark energy on a repair that his Beast Mode could do for it.Even 
if it did take longer.
It was then while he thought about damage that Tavatron suddenly popped into 
his mind, she fought much better then she gave herself credit for. She'd 
almost scrapped him, didn't she? And she knew where to hit as well, enough 
damage the central nerve system and it could kill a bot!
Dinobot crept on, it was then that the faint sent of warm fur caught his 
attention. Some sort of large mammal was near by!
He stalked into the underbrush and disappeared into the morning, breakfast 
would be soon!*
